rComments: Super great professor, participation and lecture attendance aren't mandatory, but it's worth it to go. If you're the type to skim the required readings, she does a good job at pulling out key quotes and discussing them. She mixes short-stories and full length novels which makes it easy to keep up. Really flexible on deadlines and extensions.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Amazing lectures', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Very nice prof and easy to approach. She's always willing to help out her students. Her lectures can be boring since they're mostly built around quotes & discussing it in groups. But the reading selection was phenomenal! I fell in love with so many new authors! If you enjoy Victorian lit, then you won't regret having her as a prof.

Her lectures are clear and easy to understand. She's always willing to provide help if you need it, which is great. The only drawbacks I find from her courses is that the lectures are mostly revolved around discussing quotes. This can become rather tedious, especially when there's over 8 quotes for 1 lecture.
She's fantastic, one of the best professors I have had in my undergraduate degree. Lectures are clear, fun, and discussion based. This is a must take class for any English Undergrad student.

She is extremely kind and aware that students have certain stresses at school. Her lectures are helpful and she's truly interested in things you have to say. Her grading is fair and she gives constructive comments. The books she assigns are also very interesting and you can tell that she's passionate about Victorian literature. She's also funny!
